.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2030086/\n|team2             = {{fb|UKR}}\n|goals1            = \n|goals2            = \n|stadium           = TBD\n|location          = TBD\n|attendance        = \n|result            = \n}}\n{{football box collapsible|format=1\n|date              = 16 November 2020\n|time              = 20:45 [[Central European Time|CET]] ([[UTC+01:00]])\n|round             = 2020\u201321 UEFA Nations League\n|team1             = {{fb-rt|ESP}}\n|score             = \n|report            = https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2030115/\n|team2             = {{fb|GER}}\n|goals1            = \n|goals2            = \n|stadium           = TBD\n|location          = TBD\n|attendance        = \n|result            = \n}}\n\n=== 2021 ===\n{{football box collapsible|format=1\n|date              = 2021\n|time              = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] ([[UTC+02:00]])\n|round             = [[UEFA Euro 2020]]\n|team1             = {{fb-rt|FRA}}\n|score             = \n|report            = https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/season=2020/matches/round=2001024/match=2024456/index.html\n|team2             = {{fb|GER}}\n|goals1            = \n|goals2            = \n|stadium           = [[Allianz Arena]]\n|location          = [[Munich]]\n|attendance        = \n|result            = \n}}\n{{football box collapsible|format=1\n|date              = 2021\n|time              = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] ([[UTC+02:00]])\n|round             = UEFA Euro 2020\n|team1             = {{fb-rt|POR}}\n|score             = \n|report            = https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/season=2020/matches/round=2001024/match=2024466/index.html\n|team2             = {{fb|GER}}\n|goals1            = \n|goals2            = \n|stadium           = [[Allianz Arena]]\n|location          = [[Munich]]\n|attendance        = \n|result            = \n}}\n{{football box collapsible|format=1\n|date              = 2021\n|time              = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] ([[UTC+02:00]])\n|round             = UEFA Euro 2020\n|team1             = {{fb-rt|GER}}\n|score             = \n|report            = https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/season=2020/matches/round=2001024/match=2024475/index.html\n|team2             = {{flagicon image|Flag of None.svg}} [[UEFA Euro 2020#Play-off path group allocation|Play-off winner A or D]]\n|goals1            = \n|goals2            = \n|stadium           = [[Allianz Arena]]\n|location          = [[Munich]]\n|attendance        = \n|result            = \n}}\n\n== Competitive record ==\n{{Main|Germany national football team all-time record}}\n{{Main|Germany national football team statistics}}\nGermany has won the [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] four times, behind only [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] (five titles).<ref name=\"GermanyWC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.schwarzundweiss.co.uk/tournaments/fifa-world-cup.html |title=The FIFA World Cup |publisher=schwarzundweiss.co.uk |accessdate=13 March 2012}}</ref> It has finished as runners-up four times.<ref name=\"GermanyWC\" /> In terms of semi-final appearances, Germany leads with 13, two more than Brazil's 11, which had participated in two more tournaments.<ref name=\"GermanyWC\" /> From 1954 to 2014 (16 tournament editions), Germany always reached at least the stage of the last eight teams, before being eliminated in the group stage in 2018.<ref name=\"GermanyWC\" /> Germany has also qualified for every one of the 18 World Cups for which it has entered \u2013 it did not enter the inaugural competition in Uruguay of [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]] for [[The Great Depression|economic reasons]], and could not qualify for or compete in the post-war [[1950 FIFA World Cup|1950 World Cup]] as the DFB was reinstated as a FIFA member only two months after this tournament. Germany also has the distinction of having an [[World Football Elo Ratings|Elo football rating]] of 2196 following their victory in the 2014 World Cup, which was higher than any previous champion.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eloratings.net/ |title=World Football Elo Ratings |publisher=eloratings.net |date=13 July 2014 |accessdate=3 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nGermany has also won the [[UEFA European Championship|European Championship]] three times ([[Spain national football team|Spain]] and [[France national football team|France]] are the only other multiple-time winners with three and two titles respectively), and finished as runners-up three times as well.<ref name=\"GermanyEC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.schwarzundweiss.co.uk/tournaments/uefa-european-championships.html |title=The UEFA European Football Championship |publisher=schwarzundweiss.co.uk |accessdate=13 March 2012}}</ref> The Germans have qualified for every European Championship tournament except for the very first European Championship they entered in [[UEFA Euro 1968|1968]].<ref name=\"GermanyEC\" /> For that tournament, Germany was in the only group of three teams and thus only played four qualifying games. The deciding game was a scoreless draw in [[Albania national football team|Albania]] which gave Yugoslavia the edge, having won in their neighbour country. The team finished out of top eight only in two occasions, the tournaments of [[UEFA Euro 2000|2000]]<ref name=\"GermanyEC2000\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2000/teams/team=47/matches/index.html|title=UEFA EURO 2000 - History - Germany|website=UEFA.com}}</ref> and [[UEFA Euro 2004|2004]].<ref name=\"GermanyEC2004\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2004/teams/team=47/matches/index.html|title=UEFA EURO 2004 - History - Germany|website=UEFA.com}}</ref> In the other ten editions Germany participated in they reached nine times at least the semi-finals, an unparalleled record in Europe.\n\nSee also [[East Germany national football team|East Germany]] and [[Saarland national football team|Saarland]] for the results of these separate German teams, and [[Austria national football team|Austria]] for the team that was merged into the German team from 1938 to 1945.\n\n=== FIFA World Cup record ===\n{{Main|Germany at the FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Germany FIFA World Cup record}}\n\n=== FIFA Confederations Cup record ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!colspan=\"10\"|[[FIFA Confederations Cup]] record\n|-\n!Year\n!Round\n!Position\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}*\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!Squad\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Saudi Arabia}} [[1992 King Fahd Cup|1992]]\n|colspan=\"9\"|''Did not enter''<ref>As [[1990 FIFA World Cup]] Champions</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Saudi Arabia}} [[1995 King Fahd Cup|1995]]\n|colspan=\"9\"|''Did not qualify''\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Saudi Arabia}} [[1997 FIFA Confederations Cup|1997]]\n|colspan=\"9\"|''Did not enter''<ref>As [[UEFA Euro 1996]] Champions</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Mexico}} [[1999 FIFA Confederations Cup|1999]]\n|Group stage\n|5th\n|3\n|1\n|0\n|2\n|2\n|6\n|[[1999 FIFA Confederations Cup squads#.C2.A0Germany|Squad]]\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|South Korea|1997}} {{flagdeco|Japan}} [[2001 FIFA Confederations Cup|2001]]\n|colspan=\"9\"|''Did not qualify''\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|France}} [[2003 FIFA Confederations Cup|2003]]\n|colspan=\"9\"|''Did not enter''<ref>As [[2002 FIFA World Cup]] Runners-up</ref>\n|- bgcolor=\"#cc9966\"\n|style=\"border: 3px solid red\"|{{flagdeco|Germany}} [[2005 FIFA Confederations Cup|2005]]\n|'''Third place'''\n|'''3rd'''\n|'''5'''\n|'''3'''\n|'''1'''\n|'''1'''\n|'''15'''\n|'''11'''\n|[[2005 FIFA Confederations Cup squads#.C2.A0Germany|Squad]]\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|South Africa}} [[2009 FIFA Confederations Cup|2009]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"9\"|''Did not qualify''\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Brazil}} [[2013 FIFA Confederations Cup|2013]]\n|-\n|- style=\"background:gold\"\n|{{flagdeco|Russia}} [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup|2017]]\n|'''[[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup Final|Champions]]'''\n|'''1st'''\n|'''5'''\n|'''4'''\n|'''1'''\n|'''0'''\n|'''