urce: Republican lawyer Bryant \u2018Corky\u2019 Messner weighs run for US Senate|url=https://www.wmur.com/article/nh-primary-source-republican-lawyer-bryant-corky-messner-weighs-run-for-us-senate/27262723|publisher=WMUR|date=April 25, 2019|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Steinhauser|first1=Paul|title=Messner becomes the third Republican to launch a 2020 Senate campaign|url=https://www.concordmonitor.com/Bryant-Corky-Messner-to-run-for-U-S-senate-28216993|publisher=[[Concord Monitor]]|date=September 4, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Potential====\n*[[Kelly Ayotte]], former U.S. Senator and former [[New Hampshire Attorney General|Attorney General of New Hampshire]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Ayotte doesn't rule out serving Trump administration {{!}} New Hampshire|url=http://www.unionleader.com/Ayotte-doesnt-rule-out-serving-Trump-administration|accessdate=March 15, 2018|work=UnionLeader.com|date=November 11, 2016|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NH Primary Source: Looking to 2020, key Republicans wishing for, hoping for, encouraging Ayotte|url=https://www.wmur.com/article/nh-primary-source-looking-to-2020-key-republicans-wishing-for-hoping-for-encouraging-ayotte/23714581|last=DiStaso|first=John|work=WMUR Manchester|date=October 11, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Scott Brown (politician)|Scott Brown]], U.S. Ambassador to New Zealand and Samoa, former U.S. Senator from Massachusetts, and 2014 Republican nominee for U.S. Senate from New Hampshire<ref name=\"bnhd\"/>\n*Eddie Edwards, former police chief of [[South Hampton, New Hampshire|South Hampton]], former chief of the New Hampshire State Division of Liquor Enforcement, and nominee for [[New Hampshire's 1st congressional district]] in 2018<ref>{{cite news|last1=DiStaso|first1=John|title=NH Primary Source: PAC to recruit Eddie Edwards to run for a \u2018federal office\u2019 in 2020 to launch soon|url=https://www.wmur.com/article/nh-primary-source-pac-to-recruit-eddie-edwards-to-run-for-a