 target for Republicans. Let's make sure we keep her critical seat.|work=Twitter|author=Kirsten Gillibrand}}</ref>\n; Organizations\n* [[Brady Campaign]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Kris |title=Brady Endorses Sen. Tina Smith, Sen. Jeanne Shaheen, and Rep. Ben Ray Luj\u00e1n for U.S. Senate|url=https://www.bradyunited.org/press-releases/brady-endorses-sen-tina-smith-sen-jeanne-shaheen-and-rep-ben-ray-lujan-for-us-senate |website=Brady |date=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Council for a Livable World]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Senate Candidates - Council for a Livable World|url=https://livableworld.org/meet-the-candidates/senate-candidates/|website=Council for a Livable World}}</ref>\n* [[EMILY's List]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.emilyslist.org/news/entry/emilys-list-endorses-senator-jeanne-shaheen-for-re-election |title=EMILY\u2019s List Endorses Senator Jeanne Shaheen for Re-Election | publisher= Emily's List |date=January 31, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[End Citizens United]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Muller |first1=Tiffany |title=End Citizens United Endorses Four U.S. Senators for Reelection |url=https://endcitizensunited.org/press-releases/end-citizens-united-endorses-four-u-s-senators-reelection/ |website=End Citizens United |date=August 27, 2019}}</ref>\n* Foreign Policy for America<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/FP4America/status/1131305839678185474|title=We're proud to endorse Senator @JeanneShaheen for re-election! As the only woman serving on the Senate Foreign Relations Committee and a leading voice on the Senate Armed Services Committee, Sen. Shaheen has been a powerful advocate for diplomacy-first foreign policy. #nhpolitics|work=Twitter|author= Foreign Policy for America}}</ref> \n* [[J Street PAC]]<ref>{{cite web |title=JStreetPAC Candidates |url=https://donate.jstreetpac.org/candidate-directory/ |website=JStreetPAC}}</ref>\n* [[Planned Parenthood Action Fund]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Axelrod |first1=Tal |title=Planned Parenthood issues first wave of 2020 House, Senate endorsements |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/465134-planned-parenthood-backs-dozens-of-house-senate-candidates-in-first-wave-of |website=TheHill |language=en |date=October 10, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Population Connection]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2020 Endorsements|url=https://www.populationconnectionaction.org/2020-endorsements/|website=Population Connection}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Results===\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Jeanne Shaheen]] (incumbent)\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes =\n| percentage = 100.0%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Republican primary==\n===Candidates===\n====Declared====\n*[[Donald C. Bolduc|Don Bolduc]], former U.S. Army [[brigadier general (United States)|brigadier general]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=DiStaso|first1=John|title=Bolduc launches bid for US Senate in video, calling for \u2018change, big-time\u2019|url=https://www.wmur.com/article/bolduc-launches-bid-for-us-senate-in-video-calling-for-change-big-time/28166948|publisher=WMUR|date=June 24, 2019|accessdate=June 24, 2019}}</ref>\n*Corky Messner, lawyer and former U.S. Army Ranger<ref>{{cite news|last1=DiStaso|first1=John|title=NH Primary Source: Republican lawyer Bryant \u2018Corky\u2019 Messner weighs run for US Senate|url=https://www.wmur.com/article/nh-primary-source-republican-lawyer-bryant-corky-messner-weighs-run-for-us-senate/27262723|publisher=WMUR|date=April 25, 2019|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Steinhauser|first1=Paul|title=Messner becomes the third Republican to launch a 2020 Senate campaign|url=https://www.concordmonitor.com/Bryant-Corky-Messner-to-run-for-U-S-senate-28216993|publisher=[[Concord Monitor]]|date=September 4, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Potential====\n*[[Kelly Ayotte]], former U.S. Senator and forme